attributes.additional_details:
We would like the Government to stop the proposed development of a "Super Dairy"  for over 1000 cows in the small village of Leighton near Welshpool, Powys, Mid Wales. Concerns and objections are based on:
- the close proximity (less than 100 yards) and thus threatened closure of the only primary school and community centre in the village;
- the detrimental effect on the health of the dairy herd and the local residents
- the visual impact/increased traffic and pollution of a dairy farm that is nine-times larger than the UK average;
http://www.support-calfe.org.uk/our-campaign/
